==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Corrosion
<hw>Cor*ro"sion</hw> <pr>(k?r-r?"zh?n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>corrosio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>corrosion</ets>. See
<er>Corrode</er>.]</ety> <def>The action or effect of corrosive agents,
or the process of corrosive change; <as>as, the rusting of iron is a
variety of <ex>corrosion</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Corrosion</qex> is a particular species of dissolution of
bodies, either by an acid or a saline menstruum.</q> <rj><qau>John
Quincy.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Corrosive</ent>⟦br⟧
